## 7. Integrating Oncology SDTM and ADaM Experience with RWE  
## 7. 将肿瘤SDTM/ADaM经验与RWE结合

### English

My oncology SDTM and ADaM experience is directly relevant to RWE because population definition, endpoint derivation, temporal alignment, censoring, and traceability are important in both settings.

In clinical trials, eligibility, treatment assignment, visit schedules, response criteria, and outcome assessments are protocol-defined. In RWE, these must be operationalized from routinely collected data.

Overall survival may be relatively straightforward when reliable death data are available. Real-world progression is more difficult because assessments do not occur at standardized intervals. It may require abstraction from radiology reports, oncology notes, tumor measurements, treatment changes, or registry data.

Clinical trial experience helps distinguish controlled endpoint definitions from real-world proxies. CDISC experience contributes structured variable definitions, metadata, traceability, and QC, while RWE experience adds confounding, selection bias, missingness, fragmentation, and measurement error.

