## 9. Data Fitness for Purpose  
## 9. 数据适用性评估

### English

Before conducting an RWE study, I assess whether the data are fit for the intended purpose. I review provenance, population coverage, representativeness, completeness, accuracy, consistency, timeliness, linkage quality, coding systems, exposure and outcome availability, confounder availability, follow-up length, missingness, and refresh schedules.

The required level of quality depends on the question. Claims may support hospitalization and cost outcomes but not tumor response. EHRs may provide laboratory detail but incompletely capture out-of-network care.

I also assess whether enough eligible patients and outcome events are available. Fitness-for-purpose evaluation should occur before finalizing the protocol. If critical variables are missing or poorly measured, the design or research question may need to change.

### 中文

在开展RWE研究前，我会评估数据是否适用于研究目的。评估内容包括数据来源、人群覆盖、代表性、完整性、准确性、一致性、时效性、链接质量、编码体系、暴露和结局可用性、混杂因素可用性、随访长度、缺失情况和数据更新频率。

不同研究问题对数据质量的要求不同。理赔数据可用于住院和成本结局，但通常不适合直接评估肿瘤缓解；EHR可以提供实验室细节，但可能不能完整捕捉网络外医疗服务。

我也会评估符合条件的患者数量和结局事件数是否足够。数据适用性评估应在最终确定研究方案前完成。如果关键变量缺失或测量质量不足，就需要调整研究设计、补充链接数据，甚至重新定义研究问题。

