## 22. T-Test Experience  
## 22. T检验经验

### English

I use t-tests to compare continuous variables between two groups, including age, laboratory values, change from baseline, treatment duration, length of stay, costs, quality-of-life scores, and biomarkers.

I assess independence, approximate normality, sample size, outliers, and variance equality. When variances differ, I use Welch’s t-test. For paired measurements, I use a paired t-test.

If assumptions are not met, I consider Wilcoxon rank-sum or signed-rank tests.

I report mean differences, confidence intervals, and p-values. In observational studies, I also consider confounding and may use adjusted regression.

