## 23. ANOVA Experience  
## 23. 方差分析经验

### English

I use ANOVA to compare continuous outcomes across three or more groups, such as laboratory values, costs, length of stay, quality-of-life scores, and treatment duration.

I assess independence, residual normality, and variance homogeneity. If the overall test is significant, I use adjusted post hoc comparisons such as Tukey’s method.

If variances are unequal, I may use Welch’s ANOVA. If distributions are highly non-normal, I may use the Kruskal–Wallis test.

For adjusted, repeated-measures, or clustered analyses, I use ANCOVA, mixed models, regression, or GEE rather than simple one-way ANOVA.

