## 27. Propensity Score Methods  
## 27. 倾向评分方法

### English

I use propensity-score methods to reduce measured confounding in observational comparative-effectiveness studies.

My workflow is to define the causal question and estimand, choose the design, identify baseline confounders, estimate propensity scores, assess overlap and positivity, apply matching or weighting, evaluate balance, estimate effects, and perform sensitivity analyses.

I use nearest-neighbor matching, caliper matching, variable ratios, and weighting approaches targeting ATE or ATT.

After adjustment, I assess standardized mean differences, propensity-score distributions, extreme weights, overlap, and effective sample size.

Propensity-score methods address measured confounding only and do not remove unmeasured confounding, measurement error, selection bias, or poor design.

### 中文

我使用倾向评分方法降低观察性比较效果研究中的已测量混杂。

一般流程包括：明确因果问题和目标估计量，选择研究设计，识别基线混杂因素，估计倾向评分，评估重叠性和正值性，实施匹配或加权，检查协变量平衡，估计治疗效应，并开展敏感性分析。

我使用过最近邻匹配、卡钳匹配、不同比例匹配，以及针对ATE或ATT的加权方法。

调整后，我会检查标准化均差、倾向评分分布、极端权重、组间重叠和有效样本量。

倾向评分只能控制已测量混杂，不能消除未测量混杂、测量误差、选择偏倚或设计缺陷。

