## 28. Missing Data  
## 28. 缺失数据

### English

My missing-data approach begins with understanding why values are missing and how missingness relates to exposure, outcome, and patient characteristics.

I assess missing percentages, patterns by treatment, time, site, provider, and observed variables, and whether missingness may be informative.

Methods may include complete-case analysis, missing indicators, single or multiple imputation, inverse probability weighting, model-based methods, and sensitivity analyses.

In EHR data, missingness often reflects clinical decision-making, so it may be informative rather than random.

I report the amount of missingness, the method used, assumptions, and sensitivity analyses.

### 中文

我处理缺失数据时，首先理解数据为什么缺失，以及缺失机制与暴露、结局和患者特征之间的关系。

我会评估缺失比例、不同治疗组、时间、中心、医生和观察变量下的缺失模式，并判断缺失是否具有信息性。

可采用完整病例分析、缺失指示变量、单次或多重插补、逆概率加权、模型法和敏感性分析。

在EHR中，缺失往往反映临床决策，因此可能不是随机缺失。

我会报告缺失程度、所用方法、关键假设及敏感性分析结果。

