## 36. Final Professional Positioning  
## 36. 最终职业定位

### English

My background is well suited to an RWE Analyst role because I understand both the clinical meaning of healthcare data and the technical requirements needed to turn those data into reliable evidence.

I can work across the full analytical lifecycle: clarifying the research question, evaluating data fitness, designing the observational study, defining cohorts and variables, extracting large datasets, programming analysis-ready data, applying statistical methods, assessing confounding and bias, validating results, and communicating limitations.

My clinical trial experience provides discipline in specifications, endpoint definitions, traceability, and quality control. My RWE experience adds claims, EHRs, registries, observational design, target trial emulation, propensity-score methods, missing data, and real-world bias.

My SAS, SQL, R, Python, Unix, cloud, and distributed-data experience allows me to work across data engineering, statistical programming, and analysis.

Most importantly, I do not treat RWE as only a statistical modeling exercise. Reliable evidence begins with a clearly defined question, an appropriate data source, a sound study design, transparent operational definitions, and rigorous validation. Statistical methods should support, not replace, those foundations.

### 中文

我的背景非常适合RWE Analyst岗位，因为我既理解医疗数据的临床意义，也掌握将这些数据转化为可靠证据所需的技术方法。

我能够覆盖完整分析生命周期，包括明确研究问题、评估数据适用性、设计观察性研究、定义队列和变量、提取大型数据、构建分析数据集、应用统计方法、评估混杂和偏倚、验证结果并沟通研究局限。

临床试验经验使我在规格、终点定义、可追溯性和质量控制方面具有严格的工作习惯；RWE经验则补充了理赔、EHR、登记、观察性研究设计、目标试验模拟、倾向评分、缺失数据和真实世界偏倚等能力。

我的SAS、SQL、R、Python、Unix、云平台和分布式数据经验，使我能够跨越数据工程、统计编程和分析建模工作。

最重要的是，我不会把RWE仅仅视为统计建模。可靠证据始于明确的问题、合适的数据源、合理的研究设计、透明的操作性定义及严格验证。统计方法应当支持这些基础，而不是取代这些基础。

